aa(lp266
VBasically, it works like this:
p267
aVSo, the deeper you go into the earth, the hotter it gets.
p268
aVWe refer to this as the geothermal gradient.
p269
aVThe waters could be coming from as far away as glaciers in the Andes,
p270
aVthen seeping down deep into the earth
p271
aVand coming out to form the boiling river
p272
aVafter getting heated up from the geothermal gradient,
p273
aVall due to this unique geologic setting.
